to our property when proper weather condition allow installation of an state of the art air quality control system which minimizes smoke and air particulates nonsmoking areas on our gaming floors shredding and recycling paper receptacles placed in administrate offices company history affinity gaming traces its roots to the terrible herbst oil company founded in  by ed herbst which owns gasoline stations throughout nevada california utah and arizona herbst gaming was formed by brothers ed herbst troy herbst and tim herbst to service the slot machines in their gas stations in  over the next years here‚Äôs a look at the history of terrible herbst becoming affinity gaming sands regent announced plans of acquirement by herbstherbst purchased four  casinos to include the red hawk sports bar sands regent and rail city casino for  million herbst gaming acquired primm valley casino resorts from mgm mirage now mgm resorts international for  million operations of the two companies represented  gasoline stations and  different slot route locationsherbst announced its plans to enter a prearranged chapter  bankruptcy whereby it would keep its slot routes but give ownership of its casinos to its creditors thus splitting its current operations into two holding companiesherbst would continue to manage the casinosherbst emerged from chapter  under new ownershipherbst changed its name to affinity gaming llcaffinity sold the terribles town casino and terribles lakeside casino  rv park in pahrump and much of its slots route operations to golden gaminggolden in turn sold to affinity three  casinos in black hawk colorado the golden gates golden gulch and golden mardi gras affinity sold the terribles searchlight casino and the remainder of its slots routes to jett gaming owned by the herbst family affinity sold three of its northern nevada casinos for  million to truckee gaming a new company led by affinity executive ferenc szonyaffinity gaming announced michael silberling was the new chie